'Spectral Origins of the Cosmos'- 1/1 Freehand Sharpie on bristol board (8" x 5") ... Eons ago, our wonderous molecular universe was birthed through an explosion of light energy, ever since that explosion the newly vibrating cosmos has been endlessly expanding outward into a splendor of color. The ink on this page is an attempt to show how I've seen this process happen in my head during various spiritual experiences; each time I have seen these patterns they have brought with them new understandings of myself as well as the world. Each of these encounters with what I have come to acknowledge as pure energy, has helped me to develop myself as a person & develop new perceptions of my circumstances in order to better myself & those around me; these positive experiences have given me the desire to share them with the world & driven me to create a piece of work that I truly enjoyed. I rarely start & finish a piece in the same day, even when I spend a whole day drawing I typically work on several projects at once; today was different though, this is what flowed out of my mind while I sat at my desk - I had a blast whilst filling this page & I'm thrilled with the finished product; there is a ton of positive energy radiating from this chaotic rainbow scene. ... I'd love to talk more about my work, DM me if you'd like to know more!
